---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME, SITE_URL, TAX_YEAR, AUTHOR_NAME, AUTHOR_TITLE, AUTHOR_CREDENTIALS, AUTHOR_EMAIL, AUTHOR_PHOTO } from '../lib/constants';

const title = `About ${SITE_NAME} — Founder & Editor | Mottalib Radif`;
const description = `Learn about ${SITE_NAME} and our mission to provide accurate free paycheck and tax calculators for all 50 US states. Founded by Mottalib Radif, MBA INSEAD.`;
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl dark:text-white">About {SITE_NAME}</h1>

      <!-- Author Card -->
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center sm:items-start gap-6 rounded-2xl border border-navy-100 bg-gradient-to-br from-navy-50 to-slate-50 p-8 dark:border-slate-700 dark:from-slate-800 dark:to-slate-900">
        <div class="shrink-0">
          <img
            src="/team/mottalib-radif.jpg"
            alt="Mottalib Radif, founder of TrueTakeHomePay"
            width="120"
            height="120"
            class="rounded-full border-4 border-white shadow-lg"
            loading="eager"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">{AUTHOR_NAME}</h2>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-navy-700 dark:text-navy-400">{AUTHOR_TITLE} &middot; {AUTHOR_CREDENTIALS}</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
            Personal finance and taxation expert, MBA INSEAD graduate. Specialized in US federal and state tax analysis, helping Americans understand their true take-home pay.
            I built {SITE_NAME} because I believe every American worker deserves free, transparent tools to understand their
            paycheck, plan their taxes, and make informed financial decisions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert mt-10 max-w-none">

        <h2 id="our-mission">Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
          {SITE_NAME} exists to answer a deceptively simple question: how much money will I actually
          take home from my paycheck? Despite being one of the most important financial figures in
          every working person's life, the answer is buried under layers of federal tax brackets,
          state income taxes, FICA contributions, pre-tax deductions, and local surcharges. We built
          {SITE_NAME} to make this number instantly accessible to every worker in every US state.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our mission is to provide free, accurate, and easy-to-use financial calculators that help
          Americans understand their earnings, plan their budgets, and make better financial decisions.
          We believe that financial literacy starts with understanding your own paycheck, and that no
          one should have to pay to learn what their employer is already paying them.
        </p>

        <h2 id="what-we-offer">What We Offer</h2>
        <p>
          Our platform has grown from a single paycheck calculator into a comprehensive suite of more
          than 40 financial tools covering every aspect of personal finance. Here is what you will find:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Paycheck calculators</strong> for all 50 states plus the District of Columbia, with complete federal and state tax breakdowns including FICA, SDI, PFL, and local taxes</li>
          <li><strong>Specialized tax calculators</strong> for self-employment income, bonuses, capital gains, lottery winnings, RSU vesting, cryptocurrency transactions, and Medicare surtax</li>
          <li><strong>Retirement planning tools</strong> including 401(k), Roth IRA, Traditional IRA, and HSA contribution and growth calculators</li>
          <li><strong>Mortgage and loan calculators</strong> for home buying, mortgage affordability, refinancing, auto loans, student loans, credit card payoff, and debt consolidation</li>
          <li><strong>Property tax and sales tax calculators</strong> covering every state and many local jurisdictions</li>
          <li><strong>Educational guides</strong> that explain how US taxes work, from federal brackets to W-4 optimization to the difference between deductions and credits</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Every tool is designed to work instantly in your browser with no sign-up required. Enter your
          numbers and see your results in real time. No waiting, no email capture forms, no premium tiers.
        </p>

        <h2 id="our-methodology">Our Methodology</h2>
        <p>
          Accuracy is not optional for a financial calculator. A dollar off in your estimated tax bill can
          mislead your entire budget. That is why every calculator on {SITE_NAME} is built directly from
          primary, authoritative sources. We do not estimate. We do not approximate. We implement the
          actual rules.
        </p>
        <h3>Primary Sources</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>IRS Publications</strong>: Revenue Procedure documents, Publication 15 (Employer's Tax Guide), Publication 15-T (Federal Income Tax Withholding Methods), and annual bracket announcements</li>
          <li><strong>State Revenue Departments</strong>: Official withholding formulas, rate schedules, and standard deduction amounts from all 50 state tax authorities</li>
          <li><strong>Social Security Administration</strong>: Wage base limits, COLA adjustments, and benefit calculation formulas</li>
          <li><strong>Department of Labor</strong>: Minimum wage data, overtime rules, and prevailing wage information</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Validation Process</h3>
        <p>
          Each calculator undergoes a multi-step validation process before publication. We test every
          calculator against reference implementations, verify edge cases such as the Social Security wage
          base cap and the Additional Medicare Tax threshold, and cross-check results with official IRS
          worksheets. For state tax calculators, we verify our results against each state revenue
          department's own withholding calculator where available. Our tax engine is accurate to within
          $10 per year for federal income tax withholding and produces exact matches for FICA calculations.
        </p>
        <h3>Annual Updates</h3>
        <p>
          Tax law changes every year. Brackets are adjusted for inflation, standard deductions increase,
          Social Security wage bases rise, and states modify their own rates. We update every calculator
          for the new tax year within two weeks of the IRS announcing updated figures. The current data
          reflects the {TAX_YEAR} tax year, and every page displays the applicable tax year so you always
          know which rates you are seeing.
        </p>

        <h2 id="how-were-different">How We Are Different</h2>
        <p>
          There are other paycheck calculators on the internet. Here is why we believe ours are better:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Modern design</strong>: Mobile-first, responsive layout with dark mode support. Results update instantly as you type, with no submit buttons or page reloads.</li>
          <li><strong>No accounts required</strong>: We will never ask you to create an account, enter your email, or sign up for a newsletter to access a calculator. Every tool is available immediately.</li>
          <li><strong>Privacy-first</strong>: All calculations run entirely in your browser using client-side JavaScript. Your salary, tax details, and financial data never leave your device. We do not track, store, or transmit any personal financial information.</li>
          <li><strong>Comprehensive coverage</strong>: Every state, every filing status, pre-tax deductions (401k, HSA, FSA, traditional IRA), post-tax deductions, local taxes, SDI, PFL, and city-level surcharges where applicable.</li>
          <li><strong>Transparent calculations</strong>: We show you the breakdown, not just the final number. See exactly how much goes to federal tax, state tax, Social Security, Medicare, and each deduction.</li>
          <li><strong>No upsells</strong>: We do not sell financial products, insurance policies, or investment services. We are not a lead generation site. Our revenue comes exclusively from contextual advertising that has no influence on our calculators or content.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="understanding-your-paycheck">Why Understanding Your Paycheck Matters</h2>
        <p>
          According to a 2024 survey by the National Endowment for Financial Education, 65% of
          Americans report feeling stressed about their personal finances. Yet many of them cannot
          explain the difference between gross pay and net pay, or identify what FICA stands for on
          their pay stub. This knowledge gap has real consequences. Workers who do not understand their
          withholding may over-withhold throughout the year, effectively giving the government an
          interest-free loan, or under-withhold and face a surprise tax bill in April.
        </p>
        <p>
          Understanding your paycheck is the foundation of every other financial decision. You cannot
          create an accurate budget without knowing your take-home pay. You cannot evaluate a job offer
          without understanding how state taxes will affect your net income. You cannot optimize your
          401(k) contribution without knowing how pre-tax deductions reduce your taxable income and
          affect your paycheck.
        </p>
        <p>
          {SITE_NAME} was built to close this knowledge gap. Our calculators do not just give you a
          number. They show you the full breakdown of every deduction, explain what each line item
          means, and help you understand the mechanics behind your paycheck. We believe that an
          informed worker is an empowered worker, and that financial literacy should not be a luxury
          reserved for those who can afford a CPA.
        </p>

        <h2 id="the-complexity-of-us-taxes">The Complexity of the US Tax System</h2>
        <p>
          The United States has one of the most complex tax systems in the world. At the federal level,
          you face a progressive income tax with seven brackets, Social Security tax up to a wage base
          limit that changes annually, Medicare tax with an additional surtax for high earners, and the
          Alternative Minimum Tax for certain taxpayers. On top of this, 43 states and the District of
          Columbia impose their own income taxes, each with different brackets, rates, deductions, and
          credits.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some states, like California and New York, add their own disability insurance and paid family
          leave contributions. Cities like New York City, Philadelphia, and Detroit impose local income
          taxes. Some jurisdictions tax resident and non-resident workers differently. A person working
          in New York City but living in New Jersey faces federal tax, New York state tax, New York
          City tax, and New Jersey state tax with a credit for taxes paid to New York. Calculating
          the correct take-home pay in this scenario requires understanding four overlapping tax systems.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our calculators handle all of this complexity automatically. Select your state, enter your
          salary and filing status, and we compute every applicable tax and deduction. We handle the
          edge cases that simpler calculators miss: the Social Security wage base cap, the Additional
          Medicare Tax, state-specific standard deductions, local income taxes, and pre-tax deduction
          interactions.
        </p>

        <h2 id="our-commitment">Our Commitment to Quality</h2>
        <p>
          We treat every calculator as a product that real people depend on for real financial
          decisions. That means we do not cut corners on accuracy, we do not obscure limitations,
          and we do not present estimates as facts. When a calculation involves assumptions, we state
          them clearly. When a calculator has limitations, we explain them. When tax law changes, we
          update promptly.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our commitment extends to the user experience as well. Every page loads fast because we do
          not burden it with heavy frameworks, excessive tracking scripts, or third-party widget
          bloat. We self-host our fonts to eliminate render-blocking requests to external CDNs. We
          optimize every image and use modern formats. The result is a site that loads in under two
          seconds on a mobile connection and works reliably on any device.
        </p>

        <h2 id="disclaimer">Important Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          {SITE_NAME} provides estimates based on published tax rates, brackets, and formulas. Our
          calculators are tools for planning and education, not substitutes for professional tax
          advice. Your actual tax liability depends on factors that our calculators may not capture,
          including itemized deductions, tax credits, investment income, and specific state or local
          provisions. For your specific tax situation, consult a CPA or tax professional.
        </p>

        <h2 id="contact">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions, corrections, or feedback? We welcome all of it. Accuracy depends on community
          input, and we take every report seriously.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@truetakehomepay.com">contact@truetakehomepay.com</a>
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
